inn1.comm: runs in and bowls one on a length, and gets it to dart back in a bit, Guptill defends, the umpire misses a no-ball
pushed away with an open face to backward point, Guptill is away
this time it's a no-ball at 139.8 kph, comes on nicely off a length, and is blocked away on the off side
clatter! Baz is away, takes on the free hit, it was a length ball, coming in and he swung it with the angle, and the connection was so good that it carried all the way over the midwicket boundary

the aeroplane takes off early at Pallekele, Shoaib goes through Brendon with a peach that pitches way outside off, he goes out to push at it, but to his horror it comes back a long way, and hits off stump, kept a bit low, and there was a mile-long gap between bat and pad, Baz just went pushing at it from the crease almost
138.7 kph delivery that zips off the pitch from a length, How came out a long way too, and pushed inside the line
tries the same delivery on How that got Brendon, this one is a tad shorter, and allows him to come forward and defend even as the ball came in on off
flat and pushed through on off stump, he drives it back to the bowler, who lets it through after getting his hands to it, mid off tidies up
full and around off stump, he gets to the pitch and pushes it down the track
gives it a bit more air around off stump, he gets head on top of ball and defends
the quicker one that goes straight on, he manages to get bat on ball, and gets an inside edge on the leg side
slower now, he goes back and plays it out to short extra cover
still shorter, comes slowly off the surface, but it is flat and he plays it down the pitch off the back foot, tight over

How did that miss off stump? how on earth? it was an early decision to leave, it pitched on a length outside off stump, and came back in a long way, but missed out on grazing the off stump by a whisker
137.4 kph fuller one on the pads, nudged away in front of midwicket
137.3 kph, short of a length and thuds in to the defensive bat of Jamie
141.5 kph delivery which is on target with the length, draws him well forward and he pushes it out to backward point
Shoaib goes for the sharp bounce into the body, he goes for the pull, and gets a top edge that falls well short of fine leg
bangs this in from back of a length, he defends it down the track, given as a no-ball, his foot landed comfortably behind the line, now then
the free hit is put away in style, gets the front leg out of the way, and dispatches the full delivery that eludes a diving mid off
slides straight on with the angle, hits him on the pads, going down the leg side easily
he is just firing them in, no turn, this one is around off stump, and blocked off the front foot
slower this time, and flighted a bit, goes on leg, and he comes forward to smother it
fuller on the pads, allows him to flick it in front of square leg
tossed up around middle and leg, nudged away to midwicket
worked away off the hips to deep square leg, they think about the second, but the man gets to the ball finally just in time
Shoaib has given nothing away expect those free hits, another one is on a tight length around off stump, and is pushed wide of mid off for a run
139.1 kph back of a length ball, gets it to lift awkwardly outside off, he rides the bounce to guide it to point
the slower one at 113.4 kph, lovely delivery, he adjusted to push it away to mid on, was already well forward before he spotted it
141.5 kph, a touch fuller outside off, allows him to come out and drive confidently, but short extra cover is in the way
117.1 kph another slower one, it was angled in from a length, and he had walked across to turn it wide of midwicket, but with the change in pace, he got it right to that man at midwicket
short and some width too outside off, he cannot get it away, mistimes the cut in to the ground
pushed through flat on middle and leg, pushed down the track
slides in straight on with the angle, hits him on the pads and bobs up in the air towards extra cover
draws him forward and he drives to extra cover
gets outside the line, and works it with the angle wide of midwicket, Rehman is not getting much turn and that helps
another one fired in on leg stump, defended wide of the bowler on the on side
very tight line, bang on middle stump, he brings bat and pad together and defends
comes back in a shade from a length outside off stump, and he plays it late towards extra cover
Guptill just opens up and swings through the line of this length delivery, times it well too, but right to mid off
just a bit short of length, and punched away off the back foot towards mid off

109.6 kph slower one almost gets Guptill, it was floated wide and went away from Guptill who went for a big drive over extra cover, the outside edge went flying to the right of a diving Younis Khan at slip
reverts to short of a length now and Guptill forces it off the back foot towards mid off
dear me, it was the one that comes in from off stump and Guptill awkwarly pushed it back to Shoaib who fired in a throw that was meant for Kamran, but it went right over the keeper's head for four
the arm ball almost gets him, he came down the track, but got an inside edge that just went wide of Kamran on the leg side
worked away off the pads behind square leg
pushed away to midwicket
gets head on top of ball, and defended down the track
goes in search of some room outside leg stump, it is coming in anyway,a nd he gets an inside edge as he blocks
more leg side stuff from Rehman, and this time he gets it very fine off the pads, and Younis gives it a long chase and pulls it back
continues to operate on a tight line around off stump, and he blocks it away to mid off
looks to force this one away down the ground, it came in around off stump, and he mistimed it to mid on
the ball is coming on nicely, makes a loud sound as it hits the bat, Guptill punches it away to mid on
144 kph fuller delivery that cramps him up on the stumps, he pushes it back to the bowler
lets one wide outside off stump go, and Shoaib has overstepped again

120.3 kph slower and short delivery, Guptill had backed away outside leg and set himself up for the pull, got it of the toe-end of the bat, but it still eluded mid on all the way to the midwicket boundary, very fast outfield
shoaib is not impressed, he gives Guptll the bouncer, it was high and sliding down leg side, given as a wide, Shoaib can't believe it, he has hands on hips and smiles with a 'oh-come-on' look
good work from Martin, tips this one in front of extra cover and goes through for the single
Rehman continues to fire them in, he comes forward to defend
not sure where Pakistan are going with this line, fired way down the pads and tickled away wide of fine leg
drops it a bit short and that allows him to punch it down to long off
pushes this one in front of mid on and sets off for what is in the end a comfortable run
another one going straight on leg stump, he blocks it off the front foot
pushed through fuller but again the line is middle and leg, defended back to the bowler
bowls one on a length outside off stump and it is pushed away to covers
wafts at this one from outside off stump, goes nowhere, and is beaten
this one zips away off the seam from outside off stump, draws him forward and leaves him poking at thin air, lovely start from Gul
143.2 kph, Gul has cranked it up already, hits the bat from short of a length and rolls away on the off side
goes on the front foot, gets down on one knee, and gets bat to ball too, but hits the drive in the ground and it goes to extra cover
almost ended How's misery there, drew him forward and his hard push got an inside edge that just eluded the off stump
and Guptill takes him on right away, gets one short of a length, it sits up outside off and he punches through the line sending it racing past extra cover
takes this one on the pads, it was very full and he missed out on the flick
Razzaq is on the money now, angles it in on middle and it is pushed away to mid on
lovely lofted shot from Guptill, it was not a half volley, he waited for the length ball to come on, and lifted it straight over the bowler's head, the bat came down as straight as possible
defended back to the bowler this time
pinches a single now, works it wide of midwicket to keep strike
Gul getting the shape away from outside off stump, and it is wisely left alone
opens the face to run this one down to third man

Gul ends How's misery finally after threatening to do so before, gets one spot on, full and hurrying on to the stumps with the angle, in the rut that How is in, no way he was going to hit that one, struck on the pads, and Gul's persistent appeal gets a positive decision from the umpire for Pakistan, How doesn't bother to review, was there an inside edge? there was a sound, it was also hitting middle of middle
gets well forward and opens up a bit to open the face and run it towards point
whoa, Ross goes for a big swing outside off stump, and misses the ball completely
walks too far across and misses the flick to be struck on the pads, but that looked to be going down leg
targets the stumps with a length delivery shaping in off the seam, it is turned with the angle on the leg side

Ross gets a birthday gift, it's the Kamran moment, Shoaib got the edge with a perfect delivery that zipped away just a shade, the ball flew between younis and Kamran, who initially appeared to go for it, and then did the keeper's version of shouldering arms, stood stone still, as a bemused Younis looked on
and Ross makes Pakistan pay with his favourite cut shot that bounces high over point and gives no chance to third man as well

oh I don't believe this, two birthday gifts is too much, from the same man too, Shoaib has Ross pushing at a one that held its line,and the healthy edge goes ever so slowly to Kamran who is in good position to take it, gets gloves on it, and clangs it, Shoaib can't do anything about it, boy is he distraught
pushed away to extra cover off the front foot
defended back to the bowler
punched off the back foot down the track
New Zealand are living on the edge, well there is none this time, Guptill goes poking at a back of a length ball outside off stump, and misses
length ball on the stumps, pushed back towards mid on
another outside edge, this one flies well past slip, and eluding third man, luck has totally deserted Pakistan, completely

this is brilliant stuff from Gul, the bowlers deserve credit for sticking to their job while the keeper has long forgotten his, another push-and-miss outside off stump, he is getting them to straighten and troubling the batsman
the Gul yorker arrives, and he just manages to dig it away towards mid on
gets forward to the pitch of this fuller one and pushes it past extra cover, there is protection on the boundary
good delivery, 137.3 kph, he pushes forward and blocks it away on the off side
136 kph from Shoaib, persistently bowling a tight line, another one is defended back to the bowler
143.4 kph trying for the yorker, it swings in and ends up as a high full toss on the pads, flicked away to short fine leg
getting it to angle on to the stumps, guess no point in trying for the edges now, it is worked away to mid on
bowls it wide outside off stump and he leaves it well alone
starts with a length ball outside off, shouldered arms
Taylor survives again, he is struck high on the pads by a quick delivery from Gul, swerves in to beat the bat, and Kamran fans will be pleased to know Kamran collected that one cleanly
Taylor is having a torrid time out there, he wafts at a ball outside off and is beaten once more
gets bat on ball this time, poked towards point by Taylor
this is an outstanding over from Gul, delivers the yorker, Taylor somehow squeezes it out
length ball angling into Taylor, tucked towards mid-on for a single that keeps him on strike
Taylor is testing every edge of his bat out there, no footwork as he looks to swipe a back of length ball that he under-edges, dribbles to the keeper
a touch shorter, confidently played by Taylor this time, off the back foot, pushed towards cover
length ball from Shoaib, in the channel outside off, defended by Guptill
short of length and well outside off, left alone by the batsman
slanting into middle and leg, played from the crease towards point
Taylor continues to mistime the ball, looks to drive through cover but the ball rolls back towards the bowler
full ball outside off, goes for the drive and that is edged towards third man for a single
length ball from Gul, defended towards the off side
a grunt as he delivers that one, well outside off, left alone by the batsman
length ball just outside off, nice and tight from Gul, Taylor gets half-forward and defends
more birthday luck for Taylor, he belatedly moves towards an outside off ball and prods at it, somehow the ball is missing the outside edge
more confident this time, a length ball, and he moves nicely into the drive in front of point
Razzaq returns, starts with a back of length ball that is carefully defended
on the legstump this time, Taylor shuffles across and defends that one, 20 dot balls in the 26 he has faced
once more Taylor frustrates Pakistan by fiddling outside off without any footwork, the ball zips past the outside edge
jagging in towards off, clipped towards the leg side by Taylor
Ross Taylor gives the charge after a spell of being stuck in the crease, Razzaq responds bu bowling shorter and down the leg, that's a wide
that's better from Taylor, touch over-pitched from Razzaq, Taylor gets forward and whips that over wide mid-on for four
slides that on to legstump, Taylor shimmies across and works the ball towards deep backward square leg
starts with a fullish ball, pushed towards long-on
gets nicely forward and drives along the ground towards long-off
91.9 kmh, short of length, defended off the back foot
this time it is Guptill who feels for the ball outside off, he is beaten
much more solid from Guptill, keeps bat and pad together as he defends
and another forward defensive back towards the bowler
short of length ball outside off, defended towards cover off the front foot
on middle and leg, pushed towards long-on for a single
Razzaq sprays this down the leg side for another free run
back of a length ball, blocked by the batsman to the off side
on the pads, Guptill wanted to work that to the leg side, he can't get bat on it and the ball wobbles off the pad towards point
Taylor looking more and more comfortable now, a length ball that he punches towards long-on for another ambled single
sliding down the leg side, Guptill tries to glance that and get to his half-century, no bat, off the pads and past the keeper for four leg byes
a 96.8kmh full toss from Afridi, just below waist high, the speed meant Taylor couldn't capitalise on it, he defends
back on target this time, forward defensive from Taylor
more forward defensive, this time to the leg side
punched towards long-on for a single
on the pads, tapped towards square leg for a sprinted single
fullish ball on middle and leg, pushed towards midwicket by Taylor, no run this time
full ball on middle, driven down towards long-on, that's a half-century for Guptill, he raced to 40 or so before slowing down over the past half hour
Taylor reaches across to defend that to cover
comes out of his crease and punches the ball to the bowler
short of length ball outside off, chopped towards cover by Taylor
Hafeez keeps Taylor tied down, a length ball is pushed back to the bowler
tapped towards cover for a quick single, Taylor keeps strike
Taylor continues to grow in confidence after a horrendous beginning, a hard drive through extra cover for a single
defended by Guptill off the front foot
on middle and leg, blocked back to the bowler
tossed up a touch, played towards point  with soft hands, New Zealand attempt a sharp single, the throw from Hafeez was wild, "half-a-kilometre wide," says Ramiz Raja on commentary
slaps the final ball of the over towards point to pinch a single, good work from these two New Zealand batsman
a touch short from Hafeez, Guptill is down the track but not to the pitch, defended to the leg side
whipped off the pads towards fine leg for a single that brings up New Zealand's 100
punched back to the bowler
slightly short, allows the batsman to rock back and ease the ball towards long-on
that one drifts away a touch, Guptill was reaching for it outside off, he's beaten and Kamran whips off the stumps (collects cleanly too), but Guptill has his back foot in the crease
good over from Hafeez, just two off it, the final ball is pushed to his left, he moves across to field
legspinner pitching well outside off, blocked to the off side
looks to drive this one towards mid-off, inside-edged towards the on side instead
short from Afridi, Guptill gets on the back foot and carves that towards sweeper
on middle stump, eased towards mid-on
muscled down the ground to long-on to bring up the 50 stand
final ball is on the pads, easily worked behind square for a single
length ball outside off, defended towards cover
on middle and leg, tucked behind square leg for a single
short of length ball around off, eased to the left of the bowler, who scrambled across but couldn't block it
length ball on off, Taylor wants to punch that to the leg side, but instead pushes it back to the bowler
once more Taylor blocks towards the bowler

outstanding bit of work from Umar Akmal, a direct hit from deep square leg when he was on the move, with just one stump to aim at as well, no reward for it though as Taylor has made his ground, it was a legstump ball that Taylor pushed towards deep square
short and wide, poor delivery from Afridi, doesn't get punished though, carved to sweeper cover
wide again, stabbed towards deep point for a single
much closer to off, defended off the front foot towards cover
the Afridi googly, played off the back foot towards point

wicket No. 15 for Afridi, he adopts his regulation celebratory pose with both arms outstretched, it was a flighted and full ball, Guptill moved forward and wanted to whip it to the leg side, he misses the straight delivery and is bowled, an annoyed Guptill walks off
short ball on legstump, punched uppishly towards long-on for a single

review time, Hafeez raps Franklin on the pads and on-field umpire Harper says that's out after a long long time, a tossed up delivery from round the wicket that pitched outside off, and turned in towards Franklin, who plays outside the line of that one, is struck on the pads around off and that was going on to hit middle, Taylor asks Franklin to review that, no use, Franklin's on his way
Scott Styris has made his first run of the tournament, a punch towards long-on for a single
outside off, carved towards point for a single
whips this towards midwicket, Younis dives to his right to field that one, he shies at the non-striker's end and there's no one backing up so that's a couple of overthrows
pushed wide of mid-off for a single
on the pads, defended to the leg side
a flighted delivery from Afridi, short and wide, Taylor goes hard at it, wants to hammer that past point, edges it over backward point for a streaky boundary
punched down the ground, Afridi moves to his left and tries to stop the ball by stamping on it, he can't
another drop from Kamran, outside off, Styris looks to stab it from the crease, edged and Kamran's horror day continues, Afridi is not amused
worked to long-on for a single by Taylor
took the inner half of the bat and went back to the bowler
length ball on legstump, driven to long-on for a single
just outside off, pushed to the left of the bowler, Kamran screams animatedly as Hafeez hustles across to stop ot
easy single to midwicket for Styris
played with soft hands towards cover, sprint through for a run
pushes this one through, punched off the back foot towards the leg side
short of length ball on middle, worked to long-on for one more
length ball outside off, defended off the front foot towards cover
quicker one from Afridi, 99.2kmh, on middle stump, turned towards square leg
length ball well outside off, big stride in as he defends
overpitched and just outside off, powered down the ground by Styris, long-on fields after the ball just misses the stumps at the non-striker's end
length ball outside off, more defence
way outside off, fuller one from Afridi, cracked towards backward point, 'Catch,' shouts Afridi, but the fielder can't latch on, and the ball rolls towards deep backward point
ends up on leg stump with some turn, easily picked away backward of square leg
worked away in front of square leg
slower through the air, and not much turn, played back to the bowler
walks across and uses the angle on this one ti nudge it to midwicket
Hafeez tries hard to stop this back foot punch from going towards long on, but it eludes his dive in the end
pushed through flat, and played down the track
floats it in slower and it is pushed down the track
ending on leg stump with that angle from round the stumps, nudged towards midwicket, Rehman does the fielding
eases this one on middle and leg down to long on
fired in, but a touch short, and he goes back to work it past midwicket, fifty up for Taylor, somehow he has survived and fought back
fuller and flatter, it is defended down the track
gives it some air around off stump, and Styris uses it to drive to sweeper cover
pushed through on leg stump, flicked away through square leg
fired down the leg side, Kamran collects and threatens to break the stumps, but does not
nudged behind the wickets fine on the leg side
lots of singles all around, another one picked away wide of midwicket, do offspinners have to end on leg stump?
another one on the pads, worked away to deep square leg
fuller on the legs, flicked away to midwicket
eased down to long on for yet another comfortable single
shortish on middle stump, worked away in front of square leg
whipped away off the back foot to deep midwicket, calmly done, no issues
takes a step down the track and eases in to a drive to sweeper cover
flatter and quicker outside off stump, steered away to short third man
slows it down in the air, flighted a bit fuller too, and it is blocked off the front foot
shuffles outside off stump before the ball is bowled, it is angled in around off stump, and he pushes it down the ground to long on
gets some width outside off stump, it bounces extra and he rides it to guide it away wide of third man
punched away to sweeper cover off the back foot, Gul with that stock back of a length
playing with lot more fluency now, comes half-forward and wrists this fuller one to long on just past the non-striker
short delivery getting big on Styris, who gets well outside the line and tries to pull it fine, but it goes over him and down the leg side
better from Gul, tight one on the stumps, it is played back to the bowler
stays in the crease and opens the bat face to push this short of a length ball to point, the position he got in before playing that shot, could have done much better
uses the angle from Rehman to push for a run to long on
a bit slower through the air, it pops in the air on the leg side as he pushes at it

Taylor is having a super birthday, gets away again, goes for the slog sweep now, but from way outside off stump, the ball bounced a bit more, but the top edge swirled high in the air and fell in the vacant area to the right of fine leg
fires this one in on the stumps, it is blocked by Ross
pushes this on towards covers for a single now
bowls it slower, it is still flat, and goes straight on outside off stump, Styris waited to play the cut shot, but was still beaten
rides the bounce on the back of a length ball outside off and punches it to sweeper cover
Gul goes goes for the yorker, ends up as a high full toss that is sent racing down to Shoaib at long on who does well to prevent the second
144.1 kph, and zipping away off the seam from short of a length, he goes fishing at it from the crease and is beaten
bowls it fuller and Taylor gets the square drive off the middle of the bat, but there is a point, and he gets in the way
still wider outside off stump, this time Taylor mistimes the cut to third man
good work from Kamran, stops a boundary with a dive to his right, Styris has edged an attempted drive and Kamran took it on the bounce, just reminding everyone that he is still there
faster one on the stumps, goes straight on and is pushed back to the bowler
much slower through the air, it was shipped through square leg, they take two, Afridi is not happy with the effort at deep square leg
tossed up slowly through the air outside off, he comes out and drives it to sweeper cover
Styris gets four, it was very full on the stumps, and he got the drive at the right moment, sending it racing past sweeper cover
cut away to short third man
too close to off stump for the cut, so Scott goes for the late cut, and gets it past short third man who has to put in the dive close to the ropes to reel it back in
the Powerplay does this to batsmen, he stands a foot outside leg before the ball is bowled, and looks to carve this length ball over cover, and is beaten by the extra bounce
and again, he is standing way outside leg, Gul follows him with an incutter, and he manages to push it away to long on
Gul goes full outside off, gets it to come in with the angle, and he gets an inside edge on to leg as he tries to drive wide of mid off
that's the way to do it, takes a step or two outside leg stump, gets a full delivery, and absolutely smashes it, too bad extra cover was in the way
lovely stuff from Gul, Styris goes agricultural, walking away to leg and tries to pull at the same time, gets in to too much of a tangle, Gul followed him with an angled ball, no wonder Styris missed

Gul has his man now, bowled it very full on the stumps, Scott went walking across the stumps towards the off side this time, all over the place really, missed on the flick across the line, and umpire Harper thought for a while before sending Styris on his way, they think about a review but decide against it, that would have taken out middle and leg
turned away behind square off the pads
raps him on the pads with the one that slides straight on, clearly going down leg
slows down the pace and flights it too, what control, he cuts it away to backward point
pushes down to long on for a single now, those are always available
whipped away off the pads behind square leg
angles in on the leg stump, he gets front foot across and works it away to deep square leg
angled in short of a length on leg stump, he takes it high on the pads as he misses the waft across the line
what a shot! just a push, it matters where you push them, this one was in the gap at covers, and he used the pace of the ball to his advantage and the fielders had no chance once it beat them
Gul comes up with the fast bowlers' response, digs in the bouncer, Nathan goes down underneath it
full on the leg stump, he gets in to an awkward position before getting it square off the pads
Gul loses his line this time, goes for the yorker but it tails away down the leg side
143.3 kph full ball on the leg stump, he brings down bat in front of pad and turns it towards midwicket
does not seem out of touch when he plays this shot, rides the bounce on a shortish one outside off to cut it away to third man
takes off from a length around off stump, not really, but still surprises him exra bounce, he pushes it down the track
goes for the slog sweep now, and misses this one on leg stump
pushes this one in the air on the leg side, Afridi goes haring after the ball, and stops it with the dive
Nathan gets going now, gets front leg out of the way, it was tossed up a bit, and he went through with the full swing to comfortably beat long on
gets this one wide of midwicket now

Taylor seems to be regaining his touch, down on that knee, and the ball will be picked up from the areas beyond the deep square leg boundary, bat made contact at just the right moment, and the ball disappeared into the crowd
goes for the yorker, but it ends up down leg, the batsman was there too though, and somehow squeezed it in the direction of midwicket
136 kph inswinging full delivery, looked to drive it past mid off but he is deep in the circle, and cuts it off
105.5 kph slower ball, what a climbdown from the furious pace he has worked up, dealt with nicely, waits for it to come on and plonks it in front of point

whacked! Gul went for the bouncer in to the body, Nathan used the angle and went through with the pull shot, almost as if he was expecting it, and deposited it in to the crowd over deep midwicket, phew! that was well struck alright

Gul gets him now, it is the slower one, Nathan did not pick it, went for the heave and inside edged the ball on to the stumps, the off bail is removed, that's all Gull needs as he sets off in celebration
145.6 ripper from Gul, Oram had no clue about this one as it struck him high on the pads after straightening from back of a length, too high, thinks umpire Harper
poor delivery to begin with, swinging wide full toss way outside off stump, he capitalises, and slashes it over point and into the boundary
Taylor has made Pakistan pay dearly, another full toss, this time on the pads, and Ross swings it powerfully, flat and quick, over deep square leg
141.1 kph high full toss, it's going horribly wrong for Shoaib, Taylor swivelled and hammered it miles over the deep midwicket boundary
109 kph slower one but miles outside the off stump, more woes for Shoaib, will this over ever end for him?
this was in the slot for Taylor, bouncing from a length, and he went for the big hit over deep midwicket again, but missed this time
and another one, this time he waited in the crease for this length ball to come on comfortably wide outside off stump, and carved it over cover, no chance for sweeper cover
nightmare this is for Shoaib, this one is fired wide down the leg side

Rosco is back in style, brings up his century on his birthday, with a savage pull over deep midwicket for six, he was waiting for that shortish one on the stumps, and when it arrived, he was ready and raises his bat in celebration, the dressing room stands up and applauds
comes forward and drives wide of long off
worked back to the bowler off the front foot, it was very full on the stumps
Pakistan have fallen apart in these death overs, it was a full toss, Oram came down the track to gain momentum and lifted it wide of deep midwicket who did not help by letting the ball through
fired wide down the leg side, actually Oram earned it by getting the legs out of the way
misses out on another full toss on the pads, gets too far down leg and eases it to long on
close to off stump, and steers it to short third man
Oram finishes the over on a high, backs away down the leg side, Rehman gives it some air at this moment, of all times, and Oram lifts it over long off for maximum
Ross welcomes him with a fearful slap through extra cover, made some room outside leg stump, and smashed the half volley through the off side
carnage! this has got to be stinging for Pakistan, more so after the millions of chances Ross has had, down on a knee and swings him over deep midwicket from outside off stump
walks outside off stump looking for the big swing again, Razzaq floats it wide of off stump
they just keep coming, full toss on off stump, Ross hits it into orbit, somewhere over deep midwicket, keep disappearing from the moment he bends the knee and swings them
and another wide outside off from Razzaq, Pakistan have totally lost it
goes across off stump, but misses out this time, heaving this full one down to long off, Oram lumbers back for the second
now he hits it straight down the ground, walking across the off stump, gets a full delivery in the slot, and bashes it along the ground, Afridi at long on had given up the chase long ago

30 runs off the over, Pakistan have been blown away, at Razzaq's pace the full toss comes on nicely along around off stump, and Ross gets another of those monster swings right of the middle of the bat, where has this one disappeared? it is in Taylor's zone, over deep midwicket
Oram from the other end, no respite for Pakistan, Afridi persists with Rehman, and Oram smashes it high over the long on boundary

and another one, I have lost count, New Zealand have too, they are just hitting them one after the other, Pakistan haven't even bothered to count, lifted high over long off who thought he had a chance initially, but it beat him by some 20 feet
Oram departs now, it doesn't matter, he has played his part, went for another maximum over long on, but this time it wasn't monstrous enough, and settled into the fielder's hands
four more down the ground, this time from Mills, and behind the keeper, he charges down and has a big heave, and gets the outside edge that gives the keeper no chance
Mills connects, not as well as he would have liked though, it still fetches him a couple as it falls right between long on and long off
Mills finishes off with a single down to short third man off a widish delivery, phew! this ends the slaughter

inn2.comm: Mills starts with a peach of a delivery, back of a length ball swerving away as Hafeez walks into a defensive shot
much shorter, and wider as well, Hafeez gets Pakistan away with a uppish carve over cover for four
Mills getting the ball to curve away after bouncing, this one is left alone by Hafeez
delicately guided towards third man off the front foot for a single
shortish and wide, Shehzad looks to pull that one from well outside off, mistimed towards midwicket
outstanding fielding from Jamie How, Shehzad seemed to have got that one through the gap, but How leaps to his left at backward point to cut it off
Southee starts the over with a short of length ball on off, defended

more bad news for Pakistan, Southee has struck, hang on, Hafeez is reviewing the lbw, it was pitching on off, short of length ball, hits Hafeez, who is stuck on the crease, on the knee roll, he was looking to work that to square leg, umpire Llong raises the finger, Hafeez has a long chat with Shehzad before going for the review, it may have just shaved leg stump, that decision is left to the on-field umpire, so Hafeez is gone,
length ball outside off, punched confidently towards mid-off
superb start from Southee, a back of length ball that surprises Kamran, who is hit in the thigh, that was too high to be lbw
outside off and that's left alone by Kamran
short of length once more, pushed past a diving Martin Guptill at cover, Nathan McCullum does the fielding
beaten, superb line and length from Mills, just a hint of away movement and Shehzad can't get bat on it

perhaps striving to start from too straight, it is overpitched on legstump, flicked past Tim Southee who has to chase that to the rope, just makes it in time to flick the ball back in, and some poor, poor  running from Pakistan means they get only two
back of a length and outside off, defended off the back foot
full ball, goes for the drive but misses
more defence, this time to cover, Mills not giving any room for the batsmen
a delightful drive from Shehzad to end the over, a controlled stroke sends the ball racing past extra cover
back of a length delivery on off stump, Kamran Akmal gets right behind the line to defend
a huge appeal for caught-behind, Southee getting his outswingers going, Kamran pokes at it and misses
a confident drive from Kamran, fuller and wider this time from Southee, punched but straight to cover
this time Kamran finds the point fielder
length ball on middle, eased towards mid-off by Kamran, three times he middled it and three times he has found the fielder
and that completes the maiden, a mistimed drive towards extra cover from Kamran
short of length ball, defended solidly by Shehzad
full ball outside off, works it towards extra cover
New Zealand's fielding has always been top-class, the oldest man in the squad Styris shows how it is done, a forceful drive from Shehzad is stopped as Styris dives from extra cover
pushed towards mid-off this time, soft enough to have time for a single
length ball is dabbed towards cover and a quick single is pinched
shorter and more width on offer, bottom-edged towards cover, no run, only three off the over
short of length again from Southee, angling into the batsman who jabs it towards midwicket

this might be a huge blow for New Zealand, Vettori seems to have injured himself trying to catch a miscued lofted on-drive from Kamran, he can't reach across from mid-on in time, and he's clutching his knee in pain, it's gone for four as well, he waves away the physio though
dropped, a check drive from Kamran and Southee sticks out his right hand but can't latch on to a tough chance that came at a catch-able height
works this one towards cover
Williamson has to field immediately, poked towards backward point by Shehzad
a desperate cry of 'Noooo' from Shehzad after Kamran starts haring down the track on playing the ball to backward point, Jamie How can't field cleanly or else that might have been close

Mills has got the wicket his bowling seemed on the verge of getting, once more the batsman looking to work the ball square on the leg side, a short of length ball heading for middle and off, hit just above the knee roll, Shehzad wonders about the referral, but with Pakistan having already used one up, he walks off, Pakistan are two down
Mills sticks to his policy, back of a length and around off, defended off the back foot
defended to the off side by Younis, a shortish ball just outside off

bowled him, New Zealand can do little wrong here, Mills sets off on a delighted run after getting through Younis' defences, that one didn't swing away after pitching on a length, Younis plays outside the line and the offstump is on the ground, Pakistan in tatters here
short of length and well outside off, swings away and that's left alone
end of a sensational over from Mills, getting the ball to jag away late after pitching on middle and leg, Misbah is beaten

make that four down, Ross Taylor does not return the favour to Kamran Akmal, what an ingrate, a length ball around off, Kamran looking to work the ball to leg, the outside edge flies low to first slip, Taylor wants nothing to spoil his birthday bonanza, he clasps that one and New Zealand are in dreamland
back of length ball on middle and leg, tucked to the leg side for a single
swinging away outside off, left alone by Misbah
slanting in towards leg, tucked towards deep backward square leg for a couple
short of length and outside off, left alone
fullish and wide outside off, goes for the drive and gets an outside edge which is well wide of slip and the ball hurtles to third man
outside off, rising delivery, left alone
Mills is bowling a dream spell here, length ball in the channel outside off, batsman is beaten as he looks to defend
and again the ball moves away from the batsman, who searches for the ball but can't get bat on it, terrific bowling this
shortish and way outside off, just within the allowed limit though, left alone
shortish ball on off, Misbah gets off strike by guiding that off the back foot towards third man
this one holds its line, Akmal plays inside the line of that one
starts with an outside off ball, batsman shoulders arms
once more Misbah is content to let it go
sticks to back of length, angling in and that is defended towards the off side
sliding down the leg side, off the thigh pad towards square leg
length ball outside off, punched towards cover off the front foot
Misbah plays inside the line of the final delivery of the over, shortish and just outside off
short of length ball heading towards the leg side, defended to midwicket
fuller this time, looks to work that ball towards the leg side, edged on to the pads
fullish ball angling down the leg, Misbah walks and looks to guide that, off the pads and past the keeper for four
well outside off, Misbah is not tempted into chasing that
this time Misbah is nearly tempted by a similar ball, Mills getting plenty of bounce, Misbah pondered over dinking it towards third man before deciding against it
back of length ball heading for off, keeps a bit low, defended by Misbah
Oram keeps it tight around off, blocked off the back foot towards backward point
similar ball, just a bit shorter, opens the face to guide the ball towards third man for a single
length ball outside off, Misbah gets well forward to block it
looks to defend another length ball that was homing in on off, gets an inside edge towards backward square leg
on middle stump, Misbah shuffles across the stumps and tucks the ball towards fine leg, think of a second but decide against it as Umar drops his bat

review time, an lbw appeal against Misbah that is turned down, it was a back of length ball that strikes Misbah in front of middle and leg, but on the thigh pad, replays show that is going to sail over, and New Zealand lose a review
Southee keeps pinging that offstump line, defended towards midwicket
fuller ball and on legstump, whipped down to fine leg by the batsman
again it is full, gets the ball to swing away, well outside off, batsman mistimes a drive towards cover
short ball that leaps up at Umar, who goes for the pull, gets a top-edge that soars over the keeper, lucky that
short of length ball on offstump, defended after getting behind the line
length ball outside off, cracked towards backward point, can't beat the fielder
back of length ball just outside off, defended off the front foot towards cover

lbw shout, turned down, New Zealand think about calling for a review but after much pontificating decide against it, it was a much closer call than the one they reviewed a few overs ago, strikes Umar on the pads in front of middle and off after pitching around off, height might have been the only saviour for Umar
outside off and that one is left alone
slapped towards point this time
short ball outside off, Umar leaves it to the keeper
played with soft hands towards point, Guptill slips as he moves in to field, scrape his elbows as he looks to stop the ball, no run results though
this one angles in towards middle, defended off the front foot
length ball around off, pushed towards extra cover
short of length and outside off, bottom edged towards point, timing was also amiss
there's the fifth, Pakistan have lost their middle-order rock, once more the batsman was looking to play to leg, a length ball that takes the edge and flies to gully, where Styris takes a low catch
Afridi smashes one off the middle of the bat, that was headed for the wide long off boundary, but Nathan went leaping to his left at mid off, super work
mistimes the cut in to the ground and point fields
pegs him back in the crease with a short of a length delivery that is punched back to the bowler
slapdash! Boom boom whips one very wristily over midwicket from out of nowhere, it was marginally full and he worked it away in a flash
and one more, he knows only one way, this one was angled in much more, and so he went backward of square leg with those wrists
looks to launch another one over midwicket, but sees that the length is shorter, and works it on the leg side
almost got 'em, just gets the bat down in time as a length ball jags back on the pads, flicks it away to fine leg
stays back on the crease and pushes out this one to point
bowls a gentle short of a length ball that he tries to work away but it hits him on the thigh pad
absolutely whacked! Afridi charges down the track, and with his power, gets the golf swing right over wide long on, one of the cleanest hits today, and there have been lots of them
now he goes for the pull, but there is deep midwicket around to stop it on the bounce
they steal a couple now, productive over for Pakistan, worked away in front, and by the time deep midwicket gets to it, Afridi comes back for two
gets a fuller one and drives it towards mid off, shouts 'no' as he sees Afridi is primed for some running
angled in from round the stumps, gets it to jag back in further off the seam, punched off the back foot on the off side

Afridi departs, Oram gets one to angle in from over the stumps on a length, nothing superlative about the ball, just that he played inside the line, and it crashed in to the middle stump, sliding downhill faster than an avalanche are Pakistan

he will get four gifted runs from New Zealand, it was pushed out towards cover point, and no one was backing up for the throw as it hit the stumps at the striker;s end as Razzaq came back in, replays confirm that the bat was grounded as the throw came in
goes deep in the crease and pushes it away on the off side

what is Baz upto? sheesh, he went flying horizontally to pull off a one-handed stunner down the leg side, too bad it came off Razzaq's pad as he looked to flick it fine, what an effort from the keeper
blocked in to the off side off the front foot
gently leaves Razzaq and leaves him groping at this one off a length
from round the wicket, pushed out with an open face backward of point
shaped initially for the pull, but in the end worked this shortish one away off the pads
Razzaq brings out the front foot and calmly pushes away a length ball coming in on off stump
a gentle pull, as it were, gentleness all around, harmless short ball down the leg side, and pulled away without violence to fine leg
cramped for room with the angle, blocks it away on the off side
shuffles across to use the angle now, and works it away wide of midwicket
worked away off the pads to square leg
goes for an ambitious cut on the front foot, under edges the ball towards point
strides out to meet a length ball with a defensive push
this time he cuts off the back foot, but at such times, shots have a tendency to find the scores of fielders that have packed the off side cordon
and now he goes down the ground, as straight a drive as it were, beats the bowler who is late in getting down, just pulled back inside the ropes
Razzaq casually walks across to have a push at one that goes straight in the channel outside off stump

sprayed wide outside off stump, he goes down on one knee and goes for the lofted shot over mid off, but it goes to that man on the bounce, they get a run nevertheless as the ball ricochets off a direct hit
goes back to back of a length ball and defends it
leans out and drives with a lovely flourish, even short extra cover was caught watching the flourish and not the ball as it went through him
gets forward and drives towards covers
wants to dismiss this through the off side, but mistimes it towards extra cover, he wanted the run but Razzaq was not interested at all
gets one on the pads and flicks it away to fine leg
pushed away to mid on and this time the decision is made soon, they don't go for the run
pushed out towards point
worked away off the pads towards deep square leg
whipped away off the pads wide of a diving midwicket, Umar wants two, Razzaq is satisfied with one
comes slowly off the pitch and he goes back to push it out towards point
gets forward and drives away towards extra cover for a tight run
singles coming nicely now, gets deep in the crease and works it away wide of midwicket
rides the bounce nicely to punch this lifter away wide of cover, but he is quick to run to his right and cut it off
this one tails back in a long way from outside off stump, Razzaq had decided to leave it immediately, too close in the end
pushes on the front foot and gets himself a single wide of wide mid off
punches off the back foot, short extra cover lets it go, but there are men on the edge of the circle to tidy up
more of the singles now, this time it is worked away to the right of midwicket
crashed through the covers, gets one slightly fuller outside off stump, and sends it on its way past the infield
pushed out in to the covers off the back foot
goes right back in the crease as it is dug back of a length, and brings it down towards the bowler
confidently driven to the left  of wide mid off, Nathan runs across and fires in the throw that misses at the non-striker's end
takes a step out and launches in to the drive, timed very well, but straight to covers
left alone outside the off stump now
hops on the toes to work it wide of midwicket, Umar wants two and races for the first, Razzaq ambles through instead, Umar is unimpressed
drives hard off the front foot, but the infield is swarming with fielders on the off side
gets this to angle in on the stumps, he pushes it away on the leg side
pats away a short of a length ball outside off stump towards extra cover, Razzaq just biding his time here
the short one dug in really hard, well-directed too, Razzaq just about sways out of the line in the end as it whizzes past his head
the outside edge falls short of slip now, Razzaq is just looking to defend with soft hands, and that's why it does not carry
Umar charges down the track in a hurry, and bashes a short delivery high over mid on for a boundary, then tells him to go back and bowl
defended off the back foot close to the crease
looks to work this away off the pads and sets off, rightly sent back by Razzaq, there was no run there
whipped away off the pads, but Ross is too quick at midwicket to dive to his right and stop it
punching this one down to long on off the back foot
Razzaq is leaning forward nicely in to the drives here, sends another one along the ground to sweeper cover
turning in slowly from outside off, steered away to short third man
defends a fuller one in to the off side
comes forward, takes it on the half volley and drives it wide of sweeper cover
goes across to work away one turning on the pads to deep midwicket
brilliant work at short third man, KW goes diving to his right, and fires in the throw, they go to the third umpire but Razzaq is in
played with the turn towards midwicket
very full, almost yorker length on middle, dug away towards short midwicket
comes forward to this length ball and pushes it down to long on for a run
punched away off the back foot to short extra cover
looks to launch in to this one, but with Scott, the ball arrives slowly, and he pushes it away to extra cover
rides the bounce on this one outside off to guide it to point
nice and tight over from Styris, another one finishing on middle stump, no pace to work with, played back down the track
wanted to go for the charge, it was flat from Nathan, and he remained in the crease to defend
punched off the back foot back to the bowler

Umar gives it away, he was itching to take on the spinner, got a shortish one and went for the pull, but it was a touch quicker and he was late on the shot, and got it high in the air, it took a while in coming down, and settled neatly in to the hands of deep midwicket who was quite some way in from the boundary
they all go up in appeal, he was hit on the pads as he pushed forward outside the line, it went straight on to hit him on the pads, going down leg probably
fired wide down leg, Baz cannot collect it, makes a stumping motion with the arm, the ball is stopped with a dive at fine leg
flatter and on the stumps, he cannot get it away
played out on the leg side
pushes him back in the crease, and he plays it back to Scott
pushed out on the leg side
some room and bounce outside off stump, cut away down to third man
looks to make some room and go through the off side, it is much fuller, and he drives it away to extra cover
wanted to go over midwicket, but Styris is keeping it very tight on the stumps, and he plays it away on the leg side
guided wide of third man with an open face off the back foot
fired in on middle stump, he goes back to push it down the track
fuller and just outside off stump, he slaps it wide of Franklin at sweeper cover, Nathan is wiping the ball furiously, too bad Pakistan have lost so many wickets not to take advantage of a wet ball
slips it short and wide down the leg side, Razzaq helps it on its way fine
turning in down the pads again, he works it away to deep square leg
from round the stumps to Rehman who comes out in defence
pushed through quicker with the angle, and it is punched back to the bowler
short of length outside off, slapped towards backward point
are we going to see Razzaq start hitting out now? he skips down the track and lashes the ball past extra cover for four, and he has reached 5000 one-day runs as well
yup, he's definitely in the mood now, a length ball is hammered over Styris's head for a powerful hit
length ball outside off, Razzaq has a big back lift before steering the ball to point
fullish ball is muscled towards long-off for a single
looks to open the face to steer the ball but misses
Razzaq wanted to power that to midwicket, gets an inside-edge on to the pads
a bit of flight, full ball, driven towards cover
that goes straight and hits Rehman on the pads outside off, big appeal but that one is turned down, no review

There is a review now, Harper has raised the finger for an lbw appeal, both McCullums jump up and down in appeal, length ball pitching outside off, hit him on off and was going on to hit middle, Rehman falls, Pakistan have no more reviews
stretches forward to defend his first delivery
pushes the ball towards cover to take a single and Razzaq retains strike
shortish ball that is slapped towards cover
Razzaq doesn't think this is over, he thrashes a full ball past cover for four
overpitched outside off, squeezed towards point
full toss outside off, 128kmh, Razzaq flashes at it and misses
back of length ball on middle, pushed past the bowler
slips in the bouncer, a slow one too, Gul ducks under
shortish ball that the speed gun suggests is only 89kmh, Razzaq waits and waits before swiping it towards midwicket
full toss on middle, pretty high but not no-ball high, bunted down to long-on
stylishly clipped towards deep midwicket
nudged towards square leg
hitting the blockhole this time, squeezed back down the track
and another boundary for Razzaq, makes some room and swings it inside-out past mid-off for four
length ball into middle and leg, defended to the leg side
another dot ball is dabbed towards point
Oram tests Gul with the slow bouncer again, Gul pulls and gets a top-edge towards fine leg
back of length ball that was around off, good bounce , Razzaq made room to try power that over point but gets a top edge that flies past a diving McCullum
another short ball, plenty of power from Razzaq but no timing, sends it towards mid-on for a single
well outside off, Gul looks to slash that with no footwork, he doesn't connect
Razzaq wanted to send that into orbit beyond long-on, only gets an inside-edge on to his toe, ball dribbles to the off side
reaches his half-century as a full toss is hammered behind deep square leg for four
blasted down the ground, massive amount of power from Razzaq to send a fullish ball to long-off, Tim Southee dives to stop what seemed a certain boundary
Gul also does a Razzaq, stand and deliver, swings the bat to send a slower length ball speeding to the wide long-on boundary
massive, Razzaq would have been proud of that, Mills'figures taking some serious damage, he looks for the yorker, ends as a half-volley and Gul bludgeons it for a big six over the bowler's head
make that 17 off the over, a short ball is pulled hard towards deep midwicket, a diving stop keeps the batsmen to two
Everything must go is Razzaq's policy, swings the ball toward wide long-on
slow, short ball that doesn't rise up much, Gul lifts his front leg as he pulls that to midwicket
shortish ball, following Razzaq who was making room, he can't free his arms and can only force the ball to long-on
bouncer outside off, Gul is very comfortable playing the pull, he top-edges this a bit, and Tim Southee has to sprint across from fine leg and slide to stop it
the runs are flowing for Pakistan, finally, a bouncer down the leg side, helped along to fine leg
short of length ball, sliding into middle, worked behind square leg for a single that brings up the 50 partnership
full and wide outside off, Gul caresses that one past a diving cover fielder, supremely timed by Gul for four
length ball outside off, dabbed towards point and a quick single is pinched
length ball outside off, Razzaq makes room and jabs the ball towards backward point
fullish ball on the pads, driven to mid-on
a bit shorter and a touch wider, Gul carves it to deep backward point
fuller ball is thumped towards cover
muscled down to long-off, it was an overpitched ball, Nathan McCullum attacks the ball in the deep to keep the batsmen to a single
short of length and outside off, defended to the off side, Razzaq wanted the single but Gul didn't
on the pads, Gul whips it towards short fine leg, where Southee makes a smart stop
superb delivery from Styris, in the blockhole, Razzaq looking to pull the trigger every ball now, he can only block this
length ball this time, hammered over the bowler's head, long-on is very straight and Oram gets round to stop what looked like a boundary
elegantly done by Gul, driven towards wide long-on for a single
nudged towards deep midwicket for a single
defended back to the bowler
thumped past Taylor at midwicket, a misfield from the acting captain gives a single
off his pads and down to fine leg, the partnership grows to 65
Razzaq again wanted to go for the big hit, McCullum sends it short, Razzaq checks his shot and plays it past a diving McCullum
Gul looking totally at ease here, one more ball on the pads, glanced to short fine
Styris has struck, Razzaq was looking for the Hollywood hit over long-on, can't get hold of it and it balloons in the air towards Oram at long-on, Pakistan lose their ninth
Gul's on strike now, he swings a shortish ball towards deep square leg
Stryis may be a dibbly-dobbly bowler but he wants to send a message to Shoaib, a bouncer that sails high over Shoaib

game over, Shoaib lasted all of two balls, another short one from Styris, Shoaib flails at it and gets a top edge that flies towards mid-on, Nathan McCullum gets across and takes a smart catch, and New Zealand get their third win of the tournament
